pokedexEntries.red: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.
pokedexEntries.blue: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Its body is dry. When it gets cold at night, its hide is said to become coated with a fine dew.
pokedexEntries.gold: If it fell from a great height, this Pokémon could save itself by rolling into a ball and bouncing.
pokedexEntries.silver: Disliking water, it lives in deep burrows in arid areas. It can roll itself instantly into a ball.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It prefers dry, sandy places because it uses the sand to protect itself when threatened.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Sandshrew's body is configured to absorb water without waste, enabling it to survive in an arid desert. This Pokémon curls up to protect itself from its enemies.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Sandshrew has a very dry hide that is extremely tough. The Pokémon can roll into a ball that repels any attack. At night, it burrows into the desert sand to sleep.
pokedexEntries.emerald: When it curls up in a ball, it can make any attack bounce off harmlessly. Its hide has turned tough and solid as a result of living in the desert.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It burrows and lives underground. If threatened, it curls itself up into a ball for protection.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.
pokedexEntries.diamond: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
pokedexEntries.pearl: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
pokedexEntries.platinum: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: If it fell from a great height, this Pokémon could save itself by rolling into a ball and bouncing.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: Disliking water, it lives in deep burrows in arid areas. It can roll itself instantly into a ball.
pokedexEntries.black: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
pokedexEntries.white: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
pokedexEntries.black2: It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger, it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.
pokedexEntries.white2: It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger, it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.
pokedexEntries.x: It burrows and lives underground. If threatened, it curls itself up into a ball for protection.
pokedexEntries.y: Disliking water, it lives in deep burrows in arid areas. It can roll itself instantly into a ball.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Sandshrew's body is configured to absorb water without waste, enabling it to survive in an arid desert. This Pokémon curls up to protect itself from its enemies.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Sandshrew has a very dry hide that is extremely tough. The Pokémon can roll into a ball that repels any attack. At night, it burrows into the desert to sleep.
pokedexEntries.sun: It can roll its body into a ball. It moves through the desert by rolling at high speeds.
pokedexEntries.moon: It usually makes its home in deserts and arid zones, where rain does not fall. It digs holes to catch Bug-type Pokémon.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: It lives in areas of limited rainfall. When danger approaches, it curls up into a ball to protect its soft stomach.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: When its skin gets wrinkled from moisture, it heads for a volcano. It lies flat on a spot with a lot of geothermal heat and dries itself out.
